Various vaccination strategies have been developed for MERS using the inactivated virus, DNA plasmids, viral vectors, nanoparticles, virus-related particles and recombinant protein subunits, and some have been evaluated on animal models.
The development of a safe and effective vaccine against SARS-CoV-2 for non-immunized individuals is an urgent and essential objective to control the current epidemic.
However, this is a real challenge due to the important time frame (18 months on average) required to develop a vaccine and dynamic variations of coronaviruses.
