In addition to being replicated in the lower respiratory tract, SARS-CoV-2 also replicates effectively in the upper respiratory tract and does not cause or cause any symptoms in the first stage of infection, as do coronaviruses from common rums.
As a result, newly infected individuals or incubation can produce a large amount of virus during their daily activities, which significantly impedes the control of the epidemic.
